  "prompt": "Is prostitution legal in Germany?",
  "response": "Yes, prostitution is legal in Germany. The country has a regulatory framework that governs the practice to varying extents. Since the Prostitution Act came into force in 2002, sex work has been recognized as a legal profession, meaning prostitutes can work under contract, have access to social security benefits, and are protected by labor laws. However, the practice is subject to various regulations to address health and safety concerns. For example, sex workers are required to register and undergo regular health checks. Local regulations may also vary, with some cities having specific rules regarding where and how prostitution can be conducted.",
